# 1.
```
John is analyzing strange behavior on computers in his network. He believes there is malware
on the machines. The symptoms include strange behavior that persists, even if he
boots the machine to a Linux Live CD. What is the most likely cause?
A. Ransomware 勒索程式
B. Boot sector virus 啟動區病毒
C. Rootkit 攻擊核心的惡意程式
D. Key logger 鍵盤側錄器
```
```
```
What is the most likely cause? 最有可能的原因
Ans-B
```
```
# 2.
```
Ahmed is a sales manager with a major(重大的) insurance(保險) company(公司). He has received(收到) an email that
is encouraging(鼓勵) him to click on a link and fill out a survey(問卷). He is suspicious of (懷疑)the email,
but it does mention(提到) a major insurance association(協會), and that makes him think it might be
legitimate(合法的). Which of the following best describes(描述) this attack?
A. Phishing 網路釣魚
B. Social engineering 社交工程
C. Spear phishing 魚叉式釣魚(特定對象的網路釣魚)
D. Trojan horse 特洛伊木馬
```
```
```
Which of the following best describes(描述) this attack?
Ans-C
```
```
# 3.
```
Juanita is a network administrator(管理員) for a small accounting firm(會計公司). The users on her network
are complaining(抱怨) of slow connectivity(網路速度慢). When she examines(檢查) the firewall logs, she observes(觀察) a
large number of half-open connections(半開放式軟體). What best describes this attack?
A. DDoS 分散式阻斷攻擊
B. SYN flood 
C. Buffer overflow 緩衝區溢位
D. ARP poisoning (ARP欺騙)
```
```
```
What best describes this attack?
Ans-B
```
```
# 4.
```
Your company outsourced(外包) development(發展) of an accounting application to a local programming
firm(本地的程式設計公司). After three months of using the product, one of your accountants(會計師) accidently(偶然的)
discovers a way to log in and bypass(繞過) all security(安全) and authentication(認證). What best describes
this?
A. Logic bomb 邏輯炸彈
B. Trojan horse 特洛伊木馬
C. Backdoor 後門程式
D. Rootkit 攻擊核心的惡意程式
```
```
```
What best describes this?
Ans-A
```
```
